From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@kstep.dev>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/topology: Fix sched_numa_hop_mask() for CPU-less nodes

sched_numa_find_nth_cpu() was fixed in commit 617f2c38cb5c to handle
CPU-less NUMA nodes by redirecting to the nearest node with CPUs via
numa_nearest_node(). However, sched_numa_hop_mask() in the same file
has the identical bug: it directly returns masks[hops][node] without
checking if the node has CPUs.

For CPU-less nodes, the entry in sched_domains_numa_masks is NULL
(never initialized during sched_init_numa()), so the function returns
NULL instead of ERR_PTR, violating its documented API contract. While
for_each_numa_hop_mask() handles this with IS_ERR_OR_NULL(), any
direct caller using only IS_ERR() would get a NULL dereference.

Fix this by adding the same numa_nearest_node() call as was done for
sched_numa_find_nth_cpu().

Fixes: cd9f54359c90 ("sched: add sched_numa_find_nth_cpu()")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@kstep.dev>
---
 kernel/sched/topology.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/topology.c b/kernel/sched/topology.c
index cf643a5ddedd..074cab9bdecc 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/topology.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/topology.c
@@ -2345,6 +2345,9 @@ const struct cpumask *sched_numa_hop_mask(unsigned int node, unsigned int hops)
 if (node >= nr_node_ids || hops >= sched_domains_numa_levels)
 return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
 
+/* CPU-less node entries are uninitialized in sched_domains_numa_masks */
+node = numa_nearest_node(node, N_CPU);
+
 masks = rcu_dereference(sched_domains_numa_masks);
 if (!masks)
 return ERR_PTR(-EBUSY);
